HTTPS secures communication between the client and server by using SSL/TLS encryption. It encrypts the data before transmission so that even if an attacker intercepts the traffic, they cannot read or modify the information.”

How it works (Simple Explanation):

1️⃣ Client sends request to server (HTTPS)
2️⃣ Server sends its SSL/TLS certificate
3️⃣ Secure session key is generated
4️⃣ Data is encrypted before transmission
5️⃣ Only the intended server can decrypt it

Https ensures cia triad

Difference Between HTTPS and TLS
🔹 TLS (Transport Layer Security)
TLS is a cryptographic protocol.
It provides encryption, integrity, and authentication.
It can secure different protocols (HTTPS, FTPS, SMTPS, etc.).
Works at the transport layer.
👉 TLS = Security technology (encryption mechanism)

HTTPS (HyperText Transfer Protocol Secure)
HTTPS is HTTP + TLS.
It is used specifically for secure web communication.
It runs over port 443.
Used in websites to protect user data.
👉 HTTPS = Application protocol that uses TLS for security

